<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto space-y-8">
  <!-- Header -->
  <section>
    <h1 class="py-6 text-xl font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Use YouCongress from Claude
    </h1>
    <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      You can connect YouCongress to
      <a href="https://claude.ai" class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">Claude</a>
      (any free or paid version is ok)
      to find sourced quotes and policies on AI governance, impact on jobs, etc.
    </p>
    <p class="mt-3 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      No coding or terminal commands needed. Just follow the steps below.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Step 1 – Set up
    </h2>
    <ol class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-lg list-decimal pl-6">
      <li>
        Open <a
          href="https://claude.ai/customize/connectors"
          class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
        >
          claude.ai/customize/connectors</a>&nbsp;(or click the <strong>+</strong>
        button in the Connectors section).
      </li>
      <li>
        In the <strong>Name</strong>
        field, type <code class="bg-gray-100 px-1.5 py-0.5 rounded text-sm">YouCongress</code>.
      </li>
      <li>
        In the <strong>URL</strong>
        field, paste:
        <div class="mt-2 flex items-center gap-2 rounded-lg bg-gray-100 border border-gray-200">
          <pre class="flex-1 text-sm overflow-x-auto m-0"><code id="claude-mcp-url" class="block px-3 py-2">https://youcongress.org/mcp</code></pre>
          <button
            type="button"
            class="px-3 py-2 shrink-0 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800 transition-colors focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-blue-500 border-l border-gray-200"
            data-copy-target="claude-mcp-url"
            aria-label="Copy URL"
          >
            <span class="sr-only">Copy URL</span>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              role="img"
              aria-hidden="true"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.6"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
            >
              <rect x="9" y="9" width="11" height="11" rx="2" />
              <path d="M5 15V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10" />
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </li>
      <li>Click <strong>Add</strong>.</li>
    </ol>

    <div class="mt-6">
      <img
        src="/images/claude-mcp-connector.png"
        alt="Screenshot showing how to add the YouCongress connector in Claude settings. The Name field says YouCongress and the URL field says https://youcongress.org/mcp"
        class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md w-full"
      />
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Adding YouCongress as a custom connector in Claude
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Step 2 — Enable YouCongress if it's not already enabled
    </h2>
    <div class="mt-4">
      Open <a
        href="https://claude.ai"
        class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
      >
          claude.ai</a>, click the <strong>+</strong>
      button, then "Connectors" and confirm YouCongress is enabled (you can enable or disable it from here).
    </div>
    <div class="mt-6">
      <img
        src="/images/claude-mcp-enable.png"
        alt="Screenshot showing how to add the YouCongress connector in Claude settings. The Name field says YouCongress and the URL field says https://youcongress.org/mcp"
        class="rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-md w-full"
      />
      <p class="mt-2 text-sm text-gray-500 text-center">
        Enabling YouCongress as a custom connector in Claude
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
  
<!-- Step 4 -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Step 3 — Start a Conversation
    </h2>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Open a new chat in Claude and try pasting one of these prompts:
    </p>
    <div class="mt-4 space-y-4">
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
          <p id="claude-prompt-1" class="flex-1 text-base text-gray-800 italic">
            You are a policy analyst researching AI's impact on jobs. Use YouCongress to search quotes from 2025 onwards, cluster them by argument, create a disagreement map and identify tension points. Return verbatim attributed quotes with links to sources.
          </p>
          <button
            type="button"
            class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800 transition-colors focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-blue-500"
            data-copy-target="claude-prompt-1"
            aria-label="Copy prompt"
          >
            <span class="sr-only">Copy prompt</span>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              role="img"
              aria-hidden="true"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.6"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
            >
              <rect x="9" y="9" width="11" height="11" rx="2" />
              <path d="M5 15V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10" />
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="p-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg border border-gray-200">
        <div class="flex items-start justify-between gap-4">
          <p id="claude-prompt-2" class="flex-1 text-base text-gray-800 italic">
            You're a journalist writing about the pros and cons of advanced open source AI. Use YouCongress, identify arguments, explain each of them and include alternative policies. Return verbatim quotes with links to the sources.
          </p>
          <button
            type="button"
            class="ml-4 shrink-0 text-gray-500 hover:text-gray-800 transition-colors focus-visible:outline focus-visible:outline-2 focus-visible:outline-offset-2 focus-visible:outline-blue-500"
            data-copy-target="claude-prompt-2"
            aria-label="Copy prompt"
          >
            <span class="sr-only">Copy prompt</span>
            <svg
              class="h-5 w-5"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              role="img"
              aria-hidden="true"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              stroke-width="1.6"
              stroke-linecap="round"
              stroke-linejoin="round"
            >
              <rect x="9" y="9" width="11" height="11" rx="2" />
              <path d="M5 15V5a2 2 0 0 1 2-2h10" />
            </svg>
          </button>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <p class="mt-4 text-lg leading-relaxed">
      Claude will use the YouCongress tools automatically. The first time it tries to use a tool, it may ask for your permission — just click <strong>Allow</strong>.
    </p>
  </section>
  
<!-- Tips -->
  <section>
    <h2 class="py-4 text-lg font-bold text-center bg-blue-100 rounded-lg">
      Tips
    </h2>
    <ul class="mt-4 space-y-2 text-lg list-disc pl-6">
      <li>
        If Claude doesn't seem to use YouCongress tools, mention "YouCongress" in your message so it knows to use the connector.
      </li>
      <li>
        For a full list of available tools, see the <a
          href="/mcp-tools"
          class="underline text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800"
        >MCP Tools reference</a>.
      </li>
    </ul>
  </section>
  
<!-- CTA -->
  <div class="text-center pb-8">
    <%= if @current_user do %>
      <a
        href="/settings"
        class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-md"
      >
        Get Your API Key in Settings
      </a>
    <% else %>
      <.link
        href={~p"/log_in"}
        method="get"
        class="inline-block bg-blue-600 text-white font-bold py-3 px-6 rounded-lg hover:bg-blue-700 transition-colors duration-200 shadow-md"
      >
        Log In to Get Started
      </.link>
    <% end %>
  </div>
</div>
